to the editor re the abortion debate stuck in time week in review jan 21 with the decline in party discipline in the last 30 years the terms of political debate are set by the few who are passionate and organized such groups often see issues in black and white and have an interest in drawing the lines of debate in manichaean terms the paradox as you note is that americans have a more subtle view of the abortion question than those leading the debate perniciously these circumstances empowering those least amenable to compromise make it very difficult for the public debate over abortion and public policy to reflect the scientific cultural and demographic changes that are significantly altering the landscape art vanden houten st augustine fla jan 21 2001

